scopeContent.description:
1) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-1. Group on stage. Miss Ellaline Terriss dressed as the Queen standing in centre of stage, two girls in long loose robes & wreaths on hair holding up her train. The other figures all grouped round'. 4cm x 4m.

2) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-3. Group on stage. Miss Terriss dressed as the Queen sitting on throne, a girl kneeling before her, Miss Terriss stretching out hand. Other figures all grouped round'. 4cm x 4m.

3) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-4. Group on stage. Miss Frostick standing with arms out in centre, at back the other figures grouped at each side'. 4cm x 4m.

4) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-5. Group on stage. Miss Terriss with large hat on standing in centre & a row of girls all round her with large hats on holding bouquets of flowers'. 4cm x 4m.

5) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-6. Group on stage. Miss Terriss as Queen standing in centre with little page beside her, figures each side of her in front, kneeling'. 4cm x 4m.

6) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-7. Group on stage. Two 'Pierrots', one black & one white, holding open trap door, up which a girl is appearing. Other 'Pierrots' & figures all grouped round'. 4cm x 4m.

7) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-8. Group on stage. Scene on top of roof, four figures pulling up two men by long rope. Ten Pierrots lying down in front'. 4cm x 4m.

8) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-9. Group on stage. Scene on top of roof, some cats playing musical instruments & a Pierrot also playing'. 4cm x 4m.

9) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', 12" x 10" size No 41366-10. Group on stage. Miss Terriss standing in centre in bridal dress, holding shower bouquet & a little boy in frock coat raising hat to her. Other figures all grouped round'. 4cm x 4m.

10) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', whole plate size No 41366-11. Group on stage of Pierrots blowing bubbles'. 3cm x 3m.

11) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', whole plate size No 41366-12. Group on stage. Miss Frostick standing at back on pedestal with left hand out. Pierrots group round holding palettes'. 3cm x 3m.

12) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', whole plate size No 41366-13. Group on stage. Mr Hicks sitting on ground with legs crossed, Miss Terriss standing with hands on hips. Statue at back'. 3cm x 3m.

13) 'Photograph of 'The Cherry Girl', whole plate size No 41366-14. Group on stage. Mr Hicks as Pierrot sitting on ground with legs crossed. Ten girls standing behind him, all holding long sticks'. 3cm x 3m.

14) 'Photograph of The Duke of Killicrankie, whole plate size No 41153-25. Group of two. Miss Moore sitting on edge of well, Mr Brown in Scotch dress standing behind her looking down at her'. 3cm x 3m.

15) 'Photograph of The Duke of Killicrankie, whole plate size No 41153-26. Group of two. Miss Moore with hat & coat on, standing facing Mr Brown in Scotch kilts, holding out a spray of heather to him'. 3cm x 3m.

16) 'Photograph of Miss Helen Byrne, whole plate size No 41122-2, half length in drapery round figure & over head, hands folded under chin looking up'. 3cm x 2m.
